Introduction
While working on a project in solidity, I needed to make a calculation with sigmoid. Now, anyone who has already worked with sigmoid will know that it involves the irrational number e. In this article, I will describe what problems I faced and how I tried to approach the problem from a mathematical and programming concept. Solidity does not have native support for fractional operations, rather it uses scaled version of numbers (i.e: uint256 and int256) to make operations for fractional calculation. for example, if you are to do an operation like this: let x = 1/3;
In pure solidity the result needs to be scaled to adjust precision similar to this: uint256 x = (10**18)/3;
